quran[64]{c,v,t}:
  94,1,"Have We not reassured your heart for you [O Prophet]"
  94,2,and relieved you of your burden
  94,3,that weighed down your back
  94,4,and raised high your fame for you
  94,5,"For indeed, with hardship comes ease"
  94,6,"indeed, with hardship comes ease"
  94,7,"So whenever you are free, strive in worship"
  94,8,and turn to your Lord in devotion
  95,1,"By the fig and the olive [of Jerusalem]"
  95,2,"and by Mount Sinai [of Egypt]"
  95,3,"and by this secure city [of Makkah]"
  95,4,Surely We have created man in the best form
  95,5,then We will reduce him to the lowest of the low
  95,6,except those who believe and do righteous deeds; they will have a never-ending reward
  95,7,"Then, what makes you deny the Judgment Day"
  95,8,Is not Allah the Most Just of all judges
  96,1,Read in the name of your Lord Who created
  96,2,created man from a clinging clot
  96,3,"Read, and your Lord is the Most Generous"
  96,4,Who taught by the pen
  96,5,taught man what he did not know
  96,6,"Indeed, man transgresses"
  96,7,when he deems himself to be self-sufficient
  96,8,"Indeed, to your Lord is the return"
  96,9,Have you seen the one who prevents
  96,10,"a slave [of Allah] from praying"
  96,11,"What if this [slave] is rightly guided"
  96,12,and enjoins righteousness
  96,13,How about the one who denies and turns away
  96,14,Does he not know that Allah is watching all
  96,15,"No indeed; if he does not desist, We will surely drag him by the forelock –"
  96,16,"a lying, sinful forelock"
  96,17,So let him call his associates
  96,18,We will call the wardens of Hellfire
  96,19,"No indeed; do not obey him, but prostrate and draw near [to Allah]"
  97,1,"Indeed, We sent this [Qur’an] down in the Night of Decree"
  97,2,How do you know what the Night of Decree is
  97,3,The Night of Decree is better than a thousand months
  97,4,"On that night the angels and the Spirit [Gabriel] descend by their Lord’s permission with all decrees"
  97,5,It is all peace until the break of dawn
  98,1,"Those who disbelieve from the People of the Book and the polytheists were not going to desist [from disbelief] until there came to them clear proof"
  98,2,"a messenger from Allah, reciting pure pages"
  98,3,containing upright commandments
  98,4,Yet those who were given the Scripture did not disagree except after the clear proof came to them
  98,5,"although they were commanded only to worship Allah with sincere devotion to Him, being inclined to true faith, and to establish prayer and give zakah; that is the true religion"
  98,6,"Those who disbelieve from the People of the Book and the polytheists will be in the fire of Hell, abiding therein forever. It is they who are the worst of creatures"
  98,7,As for those who believe and do righteous deeds – it is they who are the best of creatures
  98,8,"Their reward with their Lord is Gardens of Eternity under which rivers flow, abiding therein forever. Allah is pleased with them and they are pleased with Him. This is for those who fear their Lord"
  99,1,When the earth is shaken with a mighty quake
  99,2,and the earth throws out its burdens
  99,3,"and man says, “What is the matter with it?”"
  99,4,On that Day it will recount all its news
  99,5,"because your Lord has inspired it [to do so]"
  99,6,On that Day all people will come forward in separate groups to be shown their deeds
  99,7,So whoever does an atom’s weight of good will see it
  99,8,and whoever does an atom’s weight of evil will see it
  100,1,"By the galloping, panting horses"
  100,2,"striking sparks of fire [with their hooves]"
  100,3,launching raids at dawn
  100,4,stirring up thereby clouds of dust
  100,5,plunging thereby into the midst of the enemy
  100,6,"indeed, man is very ungrateful to his Lord –"
  100,7,and he himself is a witness to that –
  100,8,and he is truly extreme in his love of wealth